\series bold 
Speeding Up and Slowing Down 
\layout Standard

So far you have looked at cases where the velocity, force and acceleration
 all have the same sign (all positive).
 That is, the vectors representing each of these three vector quantities
 all point in the same direction.
 For example, if the cart is moving toward the right and a force is exerted
 toward the right, then the cart will speed up.
 Thus the acceleration is also toward the right.
 The three vectors can be represented as:
